  "text": "suggesting that the mutation may cause a delayed onset of pathological phenotype. (B) Likewise, the amplitudes of the scotopic b-wave, which reflects the response of downstream retinal neurons to photoreceptor stimulation, also began to decline in 9-month-old WT/KI and KI/KI mice compared with WT/WT mice (P < 0.05). (C) To specifically examine the cone function, the photopic a-and b-wave amplitudes were plotted as a function of light stimulus intensity (À0.7 to 2.3 log cdÁsÁm [CITATION_1] ). Similar to the results of scotopic ERG, the photopic a-wave amplitude began to decline in 9-month-old WT/KI and KI/KI mice (P < 0.05). (D) The photopic b-wave amplitude was also reduced in 9-month-old WT/KI and KI/KI mice (P < 0.05). Different sets of animals were used for ERG recordings at each time point. n ¼ 4 for the WT/WT group, n ¼ 4 for the WT/KI group, n ¼ 4 for the KI/KI group. Data are shown as mean 6 S.E.M.",
